References:
https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/getting-started/intro

- Universal standard for connecting AI with data. 
- Developed by antropic.
- Structured secure way to connect with tools and services.
- Interface between AI models and external tools
- Reduces glue code. Scales across multiple models and systems.
- Gives a boundary on what AI can do.

MCP pros:
- Dynamic tool discovery
- LLM agnostic
- Standardised security
- MCP server displays what tools are available and what they can do.


Installation:
------------
uv init
uv add mcp
